### The demand-supply ratio (a more concrete saturation check)

"Saturation" is fuzzy. A more concrete version is the **demand-supply ratio**:

> **Total short-form views in your niche ÷ viable competing Roblox games**

The numerator: search TikTok and YouTube Shorts for your niche's keywords (e.g., "fishing roblox", "horror roblox forest", "tycoon coffee shop"). Sum the views on the top 50–100 videos.

The denominator: count the Roblox games currently competing in that exact niche on the front page or in the top 100 of "Top Playing Now."

A ratio above **10:1** (10 million views worth of demand chasing every viable game) signals genuine open lane — you can ship and the algorithmic + organic discovery surfaces have room for you. Below 5:1 means the existing games are absorbing most of the available attention, and you're better off finding a sub-niche or a fresh angle.

This is rough math, not science — but it's a useful gate. If you can't articulate the ratio for your concept, you don't yet understand the niche well enough to bet 4–8 weeks on it.

